# Mode Controller — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

**Layer 2 — Mode Controller** per §2.3. Sits at the system orchestrator level and handles deciding whether an incoming query requires a full Heavy execution (multi-agent deliberation) or can take the fast path (Light execution).

## Architecture

The [ModeController](file:///c:/HelioX/orchestrator/mode_controller.py#17-82) provides two crucial orchestration gates:

1. **Pre-flight Check ([select_initial_mode](file:///c:/HelioX/orchestrator/mode_controller.py#27-58))**
   Evaluates the [QueryIntent](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/schemas.py#21-28) and the `ambiguity_detected` flag from the Analyzer. 
   - [fact](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_retrieval_engine.py#549-551) → `LIGHT`
   - `comparison`, [synthesis](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_adjudication.py#87-99), `compliance` → `HEAVY`
   - [fact](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_retrieval_engine.py#549-551) + `ambiguity_detected=True` → `HEAVY`

2. **Mid-flight Check ([should_escalate](file:///c:/HelioX/orchestrator/mode_controller.py#59-82))**
   If a query begins in `LIGHT` mode but the synthesis confidence falls below the strict 0.70 threshold, the Orchestrator will call this method and receive `True`, forcing it to restart the query down the `HEAVY` pipeline path.

